      "detail": "The system runs as an operating expense without project-level governance, capital-market scrutiny, or structured financing requirements attached. Capital-market due diligence for project finance or securitisation would typically demand independent, technically rigorous verification of key compliance claims. Operating-budget framing avoids the external due diligence requirements and investor scrutiny that more structured capital arrangements would naturally impose. The capital structure enables and sustains the lighter audit standard that produces the compliance gap."
    },
