      "value": "Annual",
      "memo": "Annual renewal cycles mean compliance is declared once per year while continuous data processing occurs between review events without ongoing verification.",
      "detail": "The compliance audit occurs annually as part of licence renewal, regulatory reporting, or standard governance calendar activities on a fixed schedule. Twelve months of continuous data processing at machine speed occur between scheduled audit events without any compliance monitoring or verification. No continuous monitoring system, real-time compliance tracking, or automated verification bridges the gap between annual audit events effectively. Annual cadence makes the audit inherently retrospective, incomplete, and structurally unable to govern continuous production processing."
    },
