      "value": "Product-line",
      "memo": "Product-line revenue dependency creates institutional reluctance to invest in deeper audit verification that might reveal compliance problems requiring expensive remediation.",
      "detail": "AI products generate significant and growing revenue that is strategically important to the processor's commercial performance and market valuation. Deeper, more technically rigorous audit verification might reveal uncomfortable findings that require expensive remediation, retraining, or commercial renegotiation. Revenue dependency creates strong institutional incentives to keep the audit at the declared, documentary level rather than pushing for technical verification. The commercial stakes of potential audit findings discourage investment in the genuine verification that might uncover them."
