      "detail": "Challenging the adequacy of the compliance audit means renegotiating contracts, potentially losing access to the model, and bearing substantial legal costs. Contractual friction and commercial dependency discourage data contributors from pushing for real, technically grounded verification of compliance claims. The cost of demanding better, more rigorous audit exceeds the perceived commercial benefit of obtaining it for most data contributors. Friction sustains the status quo of declared compliance by making the alternative commercially impractical for the weaker contracting party."
    },
