      "detail": "If the commercial relationship ends, all derivative works, models, and data artifacts created during the unverified compliance period persist. The audit cannot retrospectively account for what was derived because it never verified the derivation process or tracked derivative creation during the term. Surviving artifacts mean the exit cannot be clean because an unverified and undocumented legacy of derived works persists beyond the relationship. The compliance gap leaves a permanent, unquantifiable legacy of artifacts whose compliance status is forever uncertain."
    },
